The paper discusses the challenges of big data and its impact on the energy efficiency of networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of Mixed Integer Linear Programming (MILP) and the analysis of power savings suggest a focus on data science (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The discussion of veracity and the need to distinguish between meaningful and dirty data suggests a focus on security and cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
